'''Toni Fruk''' (born 9 March 2001) is a Croatian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Croatian Football League]] club [[HNK Rijeka|Rijeka]] and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==
In 2018, Fruk joined the youth academy of Belgian club [[Royal Excelsior Mouscron|Mouscron]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.glas-slavonije.hr/373519/6/Fruk-Iz-Mouscrona-su-mi-otvorene-sve-opcije-ali-pravi-posao-tek-me-ocekuje|url-status=dead|title=Fruk: Iz Mouscrona su mi otvorene sve opcije, ali pravi posao tek me očekuje|website=Glas Slavonije|date=23 August 2018|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180824114605/https://www.glas-slavonije.hr/373519/6/Fruk-Iz-Mouscrona-su-mi-otvorene-sve-opcije-ali-pravi-posao-tek-me-ocekuje|archive-date=24 August 2018}}</ref> Before the second half of 2018–19, he signed for Italian club [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] in [[Serie A]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tuttitalenti.com/talenti/la-fiorentina-acquista-giovane-fruk-la-scheda/|title=La Fiorentina acquista il giovane Fruk. La scheda|website=Tutti Talenti|date=29 January 2019|access-date=26 June 2025|language=it}}</ref> In 2020, he was sent on loan to Croatian second division club [[NK Dubrava|Dubrava]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nkdubrava.com/2020/10/14/4699/|url-status=dead|title=Pristigla četiri nova igrača uoči nastavka sezone...|website=NK Dubrava|date=14 October 2020|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024170349/https://nkdubrava.com/2020/10/14/4699/|archive-date=24 October 2020}}</ref> In 2021, Fruk was sent on loan to [[HNK Gorica|Gorica]] in the Croatian top flight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hnk-gorica.hr/vijesti/toni-fruk-dosao-na-posudbu-iz-fiorentine/1027|title=Toni Fruk došao na posudbu iz Fiorentine|website=HNK Gorica|date=24 June 2021|access-date=26 June 2025|language=hr}}</ref> On 17 July 2021, Fruk debuted for Gorica during a 2–0 loss against [[HNK Rijeka|Rijeka]].<ref name="Soccerway">{{Soccerway|517580}}</ref> On 26 September 2021, he scored his first goal for Gorica during another loss against Rijeka, this time a 4–3 loss.<ref name="Soccerway"/>

On 12 July 2023, Rijeka announced the signing of Fruk until 2027.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=HNK Rijeka|url=https://nk-rijeka.hr/toni-fruk-novi-igrac-hnk-rijeka-velika-je-cast-i-zadovoljstvo-sto-sam-ovdje/|title=Toni Fruk novi igrač HNK Rijeka: “Velika je čast i zadovoljstvo što sam ovdje”|date=12 July 2023 |language=hr}}</ref>

==International career==
Fruk was called up to the senior Croatia squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] on 6 and 9 June 2025 respectively.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cly3pw6nzd1t|title=Croatia 5-1 Czech Republic|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]] |date=9 June 2025 |access-date=18 June 2025}}</ref> He debuted in the same tournament against [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]] on 5 September.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Petar|last=Jenjić|title=Fruk: 'Ne trebamo drugima davati priliku da u Hrvatskoj traže priliku protiv nas'|url=https://sportnet.hr/vijesti/616287/nogomet-nogometni-svijet/fruk-ne-trebamo-drugima-davati-priliku-da-u-hrvatskoj-traze-priliku-protiv-nas/|website=sportnet.hr|date=6 September 2025|access-date=13 October 2025|language=hr}}</ref>

